ObAgent: Uncertain.

Analysis: many apache→backend 502s and simultaneous sharp drop in Tomcat log row_count indicate backend failures/unreachability, not a clear CPU/memory/disk signature. CPU rises are small-to-moderate; no heap/OOM evidence in logs. To disambiguate, check:
- whether_is_abnormal_metric("tomcat.request.duration" / "Tomcat*/request_processing_time") and whether_is_abnormal_metric("jvm.memory.heap_used_pct") for JVM CPU/oom signs;
- whether_is_abnormal_metric("net.tcp.retransmits" or interface.tx_err/err_rate between apache and tomcats) for packet loss;
- collect_trace on failing POST calls (apache->tomcat) to see upstream error type and where it fails.
JudgeAgent: No - The investigation produced multiple candidate anomalies (many hosts with elevated OS CPU at various minutes; apache02 log.error_count spike to 28 at 2021-03-24 20:37:00; Tomcat log.row_count drops at 20:34–21:00) and a hypothesis of high CPU / backend unreachability, but it did not pick exactly one component, one anomaly type from the closed set, one concrete telemetry evidence tied to a single component, and one exact occurrence datetime. Root cause not fully pinned down.

